cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes an information theoretic D2D private caching model, which involves the transmission and storage of information. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with D2D communication and proposes a caching scheme for efficient content delivery. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes two caching schemes (uncoded and coded) which involve the use of algorithms and data structures. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the privacy of user demands and proposes a scheme that involves a trusted server to collect and process user data. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with privacy and proposes a scheme that involves a trusted server to ensure the privacy of user demands.
